comment: An "effective" form of Cantor's theorem ~ canth . For any function ` F ` from the powerset of ` A ` to ` A ` , there are two definable sets ` B ` and ` C ` which witness non-injectivity of ` F ` . Corollary 1.3 of [KanamoriPincus] p. 416. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 18-May-2015.)
